results.title: How Did I Get Here?
results.description: The story of Nightcrawler's birth.

results.title: The Draco Part One: Sins of the Father
results.description: Azazel summons Nightcrawler and Abyss.  Juggernaut and Professor X talk about the abuse they both suffered as children.

results.title: The Draco Part Two
results.description: Professor X and Annie psychoanalyze Polaris.  Carter stows away on the X-Men's mission.

results.title: The Draco Part Three
results.description: Azazel vs. the X-Men.  Polaris tells how she survived the destruction of Genosha, and of how she learned she was Magneto's daughter.  Mystique escapes from Abyss.

results.title: The Show Must Go On
results.description: Peter seems to be being slowly driven insane.  We know that the Chameleon is behind everything, but Peter sure doesn't.  It's a moody psychological thriller guaranteed to make your hair stand on end.  [per next issue box]

results.title: Perchance to Dream
results.description: Relive some of the most memorable moments in Peter Parker's life.  What traumatic event sparks Peter's reminiscence?  We're not telling, but believe us when we say that you've never seen the Spidey saga told like this.  [per next issue box]

results.title: The Time Before, Part 1 of 2
results.description: Spidey chases Carnage right out of the pages of Peter Parker #13 and right into the Negative Zone.  There he teams up with the original Dusk as he fights against the tyrannical rule of Blastaar.  All this, plus Spidey dons a new costume which might just look a bit familiar.  [per next issue box]

results.title: Fast Lane, Part 2 of 4: Feel the Rush
The Time Before, Part 2 of 2
results.description: It's part two of our otherworldly tale, as Spidey joins the fight against the despotic Blastaar!  You'd expect ol' Webhead to turn to the original Dusk for help, but why is Spidey teaming with...Carnage? [per next issue box]

results.title: Fast Lane, Part 3 of 4: On the Edge
Blackout, Part 1 of 2
results.description: Adrian Toomes is back in town and is planning his most daring heist yet.  Can even Spidey beat the grizzled Vulture on his own turf--the air? [per next issue box]

results.title: Fast Lane, Part 3 of 4: On the Edge
Blackout, Part 2 of 2
results.description: Spidey and Vulture face off mano a mano!  Ordinarily this wouldn't be such a big deal, but did we mention that the entire battle takes place dozens of stories over the street?

results.title: Hero of the People, Part 1 of 2
results.description: Hmmm...Spidey in his black costume...Silver Sable..."Hoo-Hah action"...Who could be responsible for such a tale?  None other than the classic Spidey team of "Two-Fisted" Tom DeFalco and Ron "He's a rich man, indeed, who fills his life with" Frenz! [per next issue box]

results.title: Fast Lane, Part 4 of 4: Back on Target
Hero of the People, Part 2 of 2
